b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Descript is best suited for podcast editors, audio content creators, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Podcastle, meanwhile, shines for podcast creators, audio content production, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Descript describes itself as \"Edit audio by editing text with AI.\" Podcastle, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI-powered podcast creation studio.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Descript** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Podcastle is a poor choice — far from it. Podcastle excels in its own right, particularly for podcast creators and audio content production.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value text-based audio editing is revolutionary, go with Descript. If all-in-one podcast studio matters more to you, Podcastle is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
